---

## 📝 Steps Overview

This guide helps DevOps or system engineers set up Jenkins quickly on a fresh Azure VM using Ubuntu or Windows.

---

## 🔧 Prerequisites

- Azure account with active subscription
- Azure portal access
- Basic CLI or portal knowledge
- Jenkins requirements (Java, ports open, etc.)

---

## ☁️ VM Creation Steps

> These are just high-level steps. Full details with screenshots are in the Word file.

1. Log in to the [Azure Portal](https://portal.azure.com)
2. Go to **Virtual Machines** > **Create**
3. Choose:
   - **Image**: Ubuntu 22.04 LTS / Windows Server 2022
   - **Size**: Standard B1s (or higher)
   - **Inbound Ports**: Allow SSH (Linux) or RDP (Windows), HTTP (for Jenkins)
4. Add tags (optional), then **Review + Create**
5. After creation, connect via SSH or RDP

---

## 🔧 Jenkins Installation Steps

For **Ubuntu/Linux**:
```bash
sudo apt update
sudo apt install openjdk-17-jdk -y
java -version
curl -fsSL https://pkg.jenkins.io/debian/jenkins.io-2023.key | sudo tee \
  /usr/share/keyrings/jenkins-keyring.asc > /dev/null
echo deb [signed-by=/usr/share/keyrings/jenkins-keyring.asc] \
  https://pkg.jenkins.io/debian binary/ | sudo tee \
  /etc/apt/sources.list.d/jenkins.list > /dev/null
sudo apt-get update
sudo apt-get install jenkins
